All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbsoluteMovementCard
Card that will move the player to a specific space on the board.
Bank
Controls the monetary operations of the game.
Board
Game board, responsible for player movement on it.
Card
Abstract class representing a card.
CardDeck
Represents a deck of cards used in the game.
CardDescription
 
CardSpace
Space where the player draws a card.
CardType
Types of cards in the game, including Community Chest and Chance cards.
Dice
Represents a six-sided dice used in the game.
FreeParking
Free parking space where nothing happens.
Game
 
GoToJail
Represents a space that sends the player to jail.
GoToJailCard
Card that will send the player to jail.
IncomeTax
Space where the player pays income tax.
Jail
Space where the player goes when they are in jail.
Lot
Represents a property on the board.
Main
Creates an instance of the game with 2 to 4 players.
MetroStation
Represents a metro station space in the game.
MoneyCard
Card that will make the player receive or lose money.
MovementCard
Card that will cause player movement on the board.
Player
Represents a player in the game.
Property
Represents a space that can be owned by players.
PropertyColor
Represents the color of a property lot in the game.
RelativeMovementCard
Card that will move the player forward or backward.
Space
Board space.
SpaceName
Names of spaces on the game board, including properties, utilities, and special spaces.
SpecialMovementCard
Card that will move the player to the next space of a certain type (e.g., move the player to the nearest Utility space).
StartingPoint
Represents the starting point space on the board.
Utility
Represents the Electric Company and the Water Distribution Company.
WealthTax
Represents a space that makes the player pay a wealth tax.
